</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_type_checking">Type Checking</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Type checking (<a href="https://github.com/MLton/mlton/blob/master/mlton/ssa/type-check.sig"><code>type-check.sig</code></a>,
<a href="https://github.com/MLton/mlton/blob/master/mlton/ssa/type-check.fun"><code>type-check.fun</code></a>) of a <a href="#">SSA</a> program
verifies the following:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>no duplicate definitions (tycons, cons, vars, labels, funcs)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>no out of scope references (tycons, cons, vars, labels, funcs)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>variable definitions dominate variable uses</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>case transfers are exhaustive and irredundant</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>Enter</code>/<code>Leave</code> profile statements match</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>"traditional" well-typedness</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_details_and_notes">Details and Notes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>SSA is an abbreviation for Static Single Assignment.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For some initial design discussion, see the thread at:</p>
